<body class="project-page">
    <!-- @include "global/header_nav.kit" -->

    <main>
        <section class="hero margins">
            <div class="title-frame">
                <h1 class="project-title puzzle-type puzzle-auto">The Window</h1>
                <h5 class="desc">Philly's new hole in the wall</h5>
            </div>
            <img src="https://placehold.co/2880x1776.png" alt="The Window storefront animation" id="W1">
            <div class="tags-frame">
                <div class="tag">
                    <p>Logo</p>
                    <div class="squares"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="tag">
                    <p>Strategy</p>
                    <div class="squares"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="tag">
                    <p>Identity</p>
                    <div class="squares"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="adjectives">
                <p>familiar</p>
                <p>casual</p>
                <p>comforting</p>
                <p>quick</p>
                <p>satisfying</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="intro margins">
            <h5>As a people, we may not be able to agree on trans-Atlantic policies, but we can all agree that eating a delicious warm patty melt on a cold Friday night-out at the bar is the greatest feeling in the world. If given the opportunity, it could solve world conflicts.</h5>
            <h5>Can't believe that one one's given it the opportunity. ... until now</h5>
        </section>
        <section class="content margins" id="window">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/1722x1272.png" alt="Graphic summary" class="width4" id="W2">
            <p class="vert-center width2">The Window is the new take-out restaurant for Philly landmark Bob &amp; Barbara’s Lounge. B&amp;B’s feels like it hasn’t changed in 60 years because it hasn’t. The Window is an extension of that feeling, just designed in 2024.</p>
            <div class="small-img width3">
                <img src="https://placehold.co/822x822.png" alt="W animation" id="W3">
            </div>
            <img src="https://placehold.co/1272x1272.png" alt="Type lockup on food wrapper" class="width3" id="W4">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/2624x1272.png" alt="Lot's of Ws" class="width6" id="W5">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/2624x1272.png" alt="Brand interlude" class="width6" id="W6">
            <p class="width2">The menu consists of classic greasy American comfort food to soak up all the drinking. Pulling from historic diners, we designed our own custom grid by– what we like to call– “goo-ifying” the squares together. This is a technical graphic design term.</p>
            <img src="https://placehold.co/1722x1272.png" alt="Vitage diner photos flip through" class="width4" id="W7">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/1722x1272.png" alt="Gooey checkerboard" class="width4 height2" id="W8">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/822x822.png" alt="Dirty checkerboard" class="width2" id="W9">
            <p class="width2">The food at The Window is a “twist on the classics.” This twist is not to be flashy, but modern.</p>
            <img src="https://placehold.co/1272x1272.png" alt="Poster" class="width3" id="W10">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/1272x1272.png" alt="Grid animation" class="width3" id="W11">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/1722x1272.png" alt="Typeface demo" class="width6" id="W12">
            <p class="width3 narrow-text">We also developed a typographic technique that is inspired by the physics of looking through a refracted glass window pane. You see that design standing out on South Street and you go “I want to check that out, and then eat a foot-long hot dog.” It’s just a natural human reaction.</p>
            <img src="https://placehold.co/1272x1272.png" alt="Another mockup, type is important" class="width3" id="W13">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/2624x1272.png" alt="Reflection type animation" class="width6" id="W14">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/2624x1272.png" alt="Storefront menu & door vinyl" class="width6" id="W15">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/822x822.png" alt="People ordering in line" class="width2" id="W16">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/1722x1272.png" alt="People inside B&Bs enjoying the food" class="width4 height2" id="W17">
            <p class="width2">Reliable. Satisfying. Straight-forward and high-quality. Inspired by guilty pleasure foods. These are just a few of the phrases that could be used to describe the 2025 Toyota Corolla. Anyway, The Window was a super fun project and we highly recommend you visit.</p>
            <img src="https://placehold.co/2624x1272.png" alt="People outside in front of graphics" class="width6" id="W18">
        </section>
